findings_details.body:
ingestion uses 'excludeDirs.addAll(listOf(file("artifacts"), file("input-data"),))' (multi-line, trailing comma after the listOf argument), while infra/build.gradle.kts:16 uses 'excludeDirs.add(file("cdk.out"))' and lambda/build.gradle.kts:19 uses 'excludeDirs.add(file("debug-outputs"))'. Evidence: searching the repo, this is the only site that uses the 'addAll(listOf(...),)' idiom with a trailing comma after the single listOf argument (grep -E '^\s+\),$' across build.gradle.kts files). Impact: stylistic outlier in a set of three sibling files introduced together — harder to scan side-by-side. Fix: use two .add() calls to match sibling files, i.e.

idea {
    module {
        excludeDirs.add(file("artifacts"))
        excludeDirs.add(file("input-data"))
    }
}

or use the single-line form 'excludeDirs.addAll(listOf(file("artifacts"), file("input-data")))'. The two-.add() form is most consistent with infra and lambda.
